place.name: WONSTON
place.gazetteerText: WONSTON, a parish in Winchester district, Hants; 1¾ mile W of Mitcheldever r. station, and 6 N of Winchester. It contains Sutton-Scotney village, which has a post-office under Mitcheldever Station. Acres, 4,160. Real property, £7,132. Pop., 706. Houses, 150. The manor belongs to the Dean and Chapter of Winchester. The living is a rectory in the diocese of Winchester. Value, £967.* Patron, the Bishop of W. The church is modern. There is a national school. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
